FOUR people including three children are feared dead in a ghastly road accident which occurred at Kahama District in Shinyanga Region on Sunday night. Information gathered from the scene, according to Shinyanga Regional Police Commander (RPC) Richard Abwao said the accident involving a Toyata Hiace with registration number T710 AZZ and a Land Cruiser with registration number T477ATC left 15 people injured. “Four people died and three of them are children aged 3 to 5 years,” said the RPC in a telephone conversation with the ‘Daily News’ yesterday. However, he said the survivors were rushed at Kahama Town Council Hospital for medical attention. Mr Abwao said, though they were still collecting information of the accident, the conditions of the injured are not bad. He further said that drivers of the two vehicles were also rushed to the hospital.